                                            <h2 class="ez-toc-section" id="contoh-kalimat-formal-situation-neutral-situation-informal-situation">
                            16. contoh kalimat formal situation neutral situation informal situation</h2><br />
                        - informal; usually used in an informal situation with shortened form or slang words in it and done between friends<br />example:<br />- Dude, howdy? long time no see.                <br />- Do me a favour, would you? Just be invisible for a while.<br /><br />- neutral: usually used in a formal or informal situation and normally uttered by someone who's just learned the language or to someone we barely know yet. <br />example:<br />- How are you? It's been a long time since the last time I saw you.                <br />- Could you do me a favour? Just disappear for a while. <br /><br />- formal: usually used in a formal situation and normally uttered to someone respected.<br />example: <br />- How have you been, Mr.Lopez? It has been a while since the last time we met.<br />
